commit.message:
unsymlink-lib: do not prepend vardb paths with EPREFIX.

The file paths in vardb have EPREFIX.  Prepending them again results
in double prefix.  Get EPREFIX information from vardb settings because
EPREFIX could be overriden by the environment.

normpath on eroot to strip its trailing '/' and ensure matching
EPREFIX.

EROOT splitted into ROOT and EPREFIX, vardb paths are prepended with
ROOT.

Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/unsymlink-lib/pull/13
Bug: https://bugs.gentoo.org/753743
Signed-off-by: Benda Xu <heroxbd@gentoo.org>
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>

commit.message:
Allow using hard links for migration.

Enabled with the expert `--hardlink` option, use hard links for the
migration instead of a full copy; useful for space-constrained systems.

A unit test is included.

Signed-off-by: Raphaël Barrois <raphael.barrois@polytechnique.org>
Closes: https://github.com/mgorny/unsymlink-lib/pull/11

commit.message:
Add a user-defined `STAGE_TAG` for docker images.

The tests don't pass with recent stage3 (based on already migrated
profiles); this allows to fetch an ancient stage3, e.g from 2019, along
with its associated portage snapshot.

Signed-off-by: Raphaël Barrois <raphael.barrois@polytechnique.org>
Signed-off-by: Michał Górny <mgorny@gentoo.org>
